{
  "stem": "18770.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Prochnik.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Actually, I'll start with my name [LAUGHS] because I heard you introduce me as 'Proch-nick.' or something like that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's interesting because it's-- the whole past is right there. 'Proh-knik' is the way the name is pronounced.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I guess it'll never be pronounced like that again.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I knew that when I came to the United States.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But sometimes, when I hear it pronounced correctly-- the way it was pronounced in Poland-- it brings back a lot of memories.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that sort of starts everything going.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was born in Cracow, Poland, in May of 1933.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I don't remember, obviously, details going back that far, but I have a lot of memories of what, you know, of my childhood between then and the time the war, you know, send us running.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My family was-- we were obviously Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We-- my mother's side of the family was-- at that point in time, when I was born-- was very well-to-do.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had a large chocolate factory-- Suchard Chocolate, which still exists probably everywhere in the world.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a Swiss company, and we had the Polish franchise.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was born into a world of governesses, and cooks, and four or five vacations a year, and, you know, a very beautiful house in Cracow, which I think later served as headquarters for the Gestapo, as a matter of fact.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of the many ironies of life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was a very privileged life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And at the same time, my grandfather-- my mother's father, the head of this wealthy family-- was very, very Orthodox man.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in fact, we had a little shul right in the house downstairs that was used on certain-- for certain holidays.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
